{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013iRBqSgtswckkLPX214W1a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.AccessLevel;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Data;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→\n    11→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Data\n    15→@AllArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PROTECTED)\n    16→public class Article {\n    17→  @NotNull private UUID id;\n    18→  @NotBlank private String slug;\n    19→\n    20→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.TITLE_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    21→  private String title;\n    22→\n    23→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.DESCRIPTION_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    24→  private String description;\n    25→\n    26→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    27→  private String body;\n    28→\n    29→  @NotNull private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    30→  private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    31→  @NotNull private User author;\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T5mgPvkBQcRmqALKPJ2aXE","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"855c40aa-43f2-440b-bdb1-674a392db18f"}
