{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NnxkJm7V262ptsgDYyPe5z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.AccessLevel;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Data;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→\n    11→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Data\n    15→@AllArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PROTECTED)\n    16→public class Article {\n    17→  @NotNull private UUID id;\n    18→  @NotBlank private String slug;\n    19→\n    20→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.TITLE_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    21→  private String title;\n    22→\n    23→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.DESCRIPTION_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    24→  private String description;\n    25→\n    26→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    27→  private String body;\n    28→\n    29→  @NotNull private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    30→  private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    31→  @NotNull private User author;\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TB8JTL5RFZ8sspb9gB2SdG","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"bbfbe065-f075-4580-b32d-b781c8a5570b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HFVjiUKhAqEUUWEe8sPWmN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class ArticleModelBuilder {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    16→\n    17→    public Article build(String slug, String title, String description, String body, User author) {\n    18→        final var createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();\n    19→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    20→                new Article(\n    21→                        UUID.randomUUID(), slug, title, description, body, createdAt, createdAt, author));\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public Article build(\n    25→            UUID id,\n    26→            String slug,\n    27→            String title,\n    28→            String description,\n    29→            String body,\n    30→            LocalDateTime createdAt,\n    31→            LocalDateTime updatedAt,\n    32→            User author) {\n    33→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    34→                new Article(id, slug, title, description, body, createdAt, updatedAt, author));\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TB8JTL5RFZ8sspb9gB2SdG","session_id":"1968c9d1-922