{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BogaWJ1oZrF5QV9ZZNV64g","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticlesByFilter;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindArticlesByFilterImpl implements FindArticlesByFilter {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public PageResult<Article> handle(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    19→        return articleRepository.findArticlesByFilter(articleFilter);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"734100c4-ba5c-4226-a5f9-2787ccd1be10"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012n4zkVHKG7bGwwHmB6JzWk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindMostRecentArticlesByFilterImpl implements FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public PageResult<Article> handle(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    19→        return articleRepository.findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(articleFilter);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"c9bf26bf-8fb7-42be-b358-e9c3c9bf2deb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GWS7aqbMrJ7TPQ2eJgEdSg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.NewCommentInput;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class CreateCommentImpl implements CreateComment {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public Comment handle(NewCommentInput newCommentInput) {\n    27→        final var author = findUserById.handle(newCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    28→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(newCommentInput.getArticleSlug());\n    29→        final var comment = commentBuilder.build(author, article, newCommentInput.getBody());\n    30→        commentRepository.save(comment);\n    31→        return comment;\n    32→    }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"6bce3321-9a39-4c76-85b1-91444a133ab2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fxob7wT9MdhFm8LRxP82KB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class DeleteCommentImpl implements DeleteComment {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public void handle(DeleteCommentInput deleteCommentInput) {\n    20→        final var comment =\n    21→                findCommentByIdAndAuthor.handle(\n    22→                        deleteCommentInput.getCommentId(), deleteCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    23→        commentRepository.delete(comment);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"613b9b28-77ef-4b82-874c-c46f48597671"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014VrD5XNKQqctLrH9G4U66T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentsByArticleSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl implements FindCommentsByArticleSlug {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    19→\n    20→    @Override\n    21→    public List<Comment> handle(String slug) {\n    22→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n    23→        return commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"fad1859e-1efb-4396-8773-c99a632e3a1b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N819nDAHFRzLo9x2tskGuU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.CommentNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl implements FindCommentByIdAndAuthor {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Comment handle(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    20→        return commentRepository\n    21→                .findByIdAndAuthor(commentId, authorId)\n    22→                .orElseThrow(CommentNotFoundException::new);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"9ef13e8c-901b-45cd-88d6-1e9cbb582700"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CtLuBfZ2q9iRdwwzwKnZRV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FavoriteArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FavoriteArticleImpl implements FavoriteArticle {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public FavoriteRelationship handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    26→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    27→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    28→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    29→        return favoriteRelationshipOptional.orElseGet(() -> createFavoriteRelationship(currentUserId, article));\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    private FavoriteRelationship createFavoriteRelationship(UUID currentUserId, Article article) {\n    33→        final var user = findUserById.handle(currentUserId);\n    34→        final var favoriteRelationship = new FavoriteRelationship(user, article);\n    35→        favoriteRelationshipRepository.save(favoriteRelationship);\n    36→        return favoriteRelationship;\n    37→    }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"f65d3a23-89a7-46c4-a0ce-b45e08d5d780"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018T5D6mdnu1GKksUdGMvnRB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    22→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    23→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    24→        favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"764d781b-9930-4aac-9860-d0b02327c595"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017huPzWTMEZoTR6bsPwQYhq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n    22→        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"b1e5beb6-d4a3-4ed0-b831-d3363b2314de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fh3GmscT1ZeK7tQuQzyXKB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsArticleFavorited;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class IsArticleFavoritedImpl implements IsArticleFavorited {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public boolean handle(Article article, UUID currentUserId) {\n    19→        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.isFavorited(article, currentUserId);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"2010d9db-6d9f-4dfd-ba1d-a227f31a27fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FtgdcAj6zqDspv49ycRDar","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.UUID;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class FollowUserByUsernameImpl implements FollowUserByUsername {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public FollowRelationship handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    25→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    26→        final var userToFollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    27→        final var followingRelationship = new FollowRelationship(loggedUser, userToFollow);\n    28→        usersFollowedRepository.save(followingRelationship);\n    29→        return followingRelationship;\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"6b28fdc7-d3f5-4729-8d5f-29c454a60bec"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K4ERxHvMhAJy2yUBb95bk7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl implements UnfollowUserByUsername {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public void handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    24→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    25→        final var userToUnfollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    26→        final var followingRelationship =\n    27→                followRelationshipRepository.findByUsers(loggedUser, userToUnfollow).orElseThrow();\n    28→        followRelationshipRepository.remove(followingRelationship);\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"be1808b5-f30d-4767-b120-d6b886dffee5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015CmFJfbdSTDqpKwam4jYgD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsFollowingUser;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.UUID;\n     9→\n    10→@Dependent\n    11→public class IsFollowingUserImpl implements IsFollowingUser {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public boolean handle(UUID currentUserId, UUID followedUserId) {\n    18→        return usersFollowedRepository.isFollowing(currentUserId, followedUserId);\n    19→    }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"ecbdb6cf-5540-41fb-abb9-7a97bc719288"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KKfWkPQxf9ncJAgmgMHxk3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class CreateTagImpl implements CreateTag {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Tag handle(String name) {\n    20→        final var tag = tagBuilder.build(name);\n    21→        tagRepository.save(tag);\n    22→        return tag;\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"75eccf3e-d201-441f-8d10-f7070e0e30db"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KY3WoVvayhYSTokGpPDqxJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindTagsImpl implements FindTags {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public List<Tag> handle() {\n    19→        return tagRepository.findAllTags();\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"26a456d1-76f0-455b-aaac-6f2bd90665be"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G5qRku3wLwxBruaS6pVtnC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.LinkedList;\n    11→import java.util.List;\n    12→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl implements FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private CreateTag createTag;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public List<Tag> handle(List<String> names) {\n    24→        final var tags = tagRepository.findByNames(names);\n    25→        tags.addAll(createTags(nonexistent(tags, names)));\n    26→        return tags;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    private List<Tag> createTags(List<String> names) {\n    30→        final var tags = new LinkedList<Tag>();\n    31→        names.forEach(name -> tags.add(createTag.handle(name)));\n    32→        return tags;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    private List<String> nonexistent(List<Tag> existing, List<String> allNames) {\n    36→        return allNames.stream()\n    37→                .filter(name -> existing.stream().noneMatch(tag -> tag.getName().equalsIgnoreCase(name)))\n    38→                .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    39→    }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"4722e922-8840-4af6-95f1-82e8baf10068"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0183WSwoHEW9VsW8mstQBU9v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleTagsImpl implements FindArticleTags {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public List<Tag> handle(Article article) {\n    20→        return tagRelationshipRepository.findArticleTags(article);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"3ad6c788-1981-419b-9d9f-e08aa5ad477f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EMmtYDD43Q7ZJFH9NDXhT6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class CreateSlugByTitleImpl implements CreateSlugByTitle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private SlugProvider slugProvider;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public String handle(String title) {\n    21→        String slug = slugProvider.slugify(title);\n    22→        if (articleRepository.existsBySlug(slug)) {\n    23→            slug += UUID.randomUUID().toString();\n    24→        }\n    25→        return slug;\n    26→    }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015U5m51t7rLRwmgeToGbax9","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"42ea8d44-f61c-4a86-82e8-4895a02d3855"}
