{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_018b5k4cRRiPVjpSeGvLxeNb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013BUQpEGNWfmMgo2faX9RTt","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Write Spring Boot pom.xml and configs","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need you to write the following files for a Jakarta EE to Spring Boot migration. The project root is at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\n## File 1: pom.xml (overwrite existing)\nWrite a new pom.xml for Spring Boot 3.2.5 with Java 21. Use spring-boot-starter-parent. Include:\n- spring-boot-starter-web\n- spring-boot-starter-data-jpa\n- spring-boot-starter-validation\n- postgresql (managed by parent)\n- com.auth0:java-jwt:4.5.0 \n- commons-lang3 (managed by parent)\n- com.github.slugify:slugify:3.0.7\n- at.favre.lib:bcrypt:0.10.2\n- jackson-datatype-jsr310 (managed by parent)\n- lombok (provided, managed by parent)\n- spring-boot-starter-test (test scope)\n- Packaging: jar (not war)\n- spring-boot-maven-plugin with lombok exclude\n- artifactId: realworld-spring\n\n## File 2: src/main/resources/application.properties (new file)\nCreate application.properties with:\n- server.port=8080\n- server.servlet.context-path=/api\n- spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\n- spring.datasource.username=postgres_user\n- spring.datasource.password=S3cret\n- spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\n- spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n- spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n- spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\n- spring.jackson.serialization.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n- spring.jackson.deserialization.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n- jwt.issuer=users-service\n- jwt.secret=secret123\n- jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n\n## File 3: src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java (overwrite)\nConvert from Jakarta RS Application to Spring Boot main class:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.domain.EntityScan;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.EnableTransactionManagement;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n@EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\n@EnableTransactionManagement\npublic class App {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease write all three files using the Write tool. The pom.xml file already exists (has been read), the others are new or existing."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3283,"cache_read_input_tokens":122905,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3283,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":935},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"8487ec2b-557d-469e-9eba-9a6539395d79"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to write the following files for a Jakarta EE to Spring Boot migration. The project root is at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\n## File 1: pom.xml (overwrite existing)\nWrite a new pom.xml for Spring Boot 3.2.5 with Java 21. Use spring-boot-starter-parent. Include:\n- spring-boot-starter-web\n- spring-boot-starter-data-jpa\n- spring-boot-starter-validation\n- postgresql (managed by parent)\n- com.auth0:java-jwt:4.5.0 \n- commons-lang3 (managed by parent)\n- com.github.slugify:slugify:3.0.7\n- at.favre.lib:bcrypt:0.10.2\n- jackson-datatype-jsr310 (managed by parent)\n- lombok (provided, managed by parent)\n- spring-boot-starter-test (test scope)\n- Packaging: jar (not war)\n- spring-boot-maven-plugin with lombok exclude\n- artifactId: realworld-spring\n\n## File 2: src/main/resources/application.properties (new file)\nCreate application.properties with:\n- server.port=8080\n- server.servlet.context-path=/api\n- spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\n- spring.datasource.username=postgres_user\n- spring.datasource.password=S3cret\n- spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\n- spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n- spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n- spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\n- spring.jackson.serialization.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n- spring.jackson.deserialization.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n- jwt.issuer=users-service\n- jwt.secret=secret123\n- jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n\n## File 3: src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/App.java (overwrite)\nConvert from Jakarta RS Application to Spring Boot main class:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.domain.EntityScan;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.EnableTransactionManagement;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n@EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\n@EnableTransactionManagement\npublic class App {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease write all three files using the Write tool. The pom.xml file already exists (has been read), the others are new or existing."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013BUQpEGNWfmMgo2faX9RTt","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"82f82af9-89e1-406d-9fa1-11de3c512491"}
