{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CvdG2Rxx8HzcuJQZgJdFDx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Eh4ku11KtkK62EAjxkMd6v","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor controllers and security","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version. \n\nCRITICAL: The API currently uses a wrapper pattern for request bodies (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}` wrapping) and a `@JsonRootName` pattern for responses. The wrapping/unwrapping in the original Jakarta version is done via two ObjectMapper beans - one with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled and one without. In Spring Boot, we will NOT use the global Jackson WRAP_ROOT_VALUE settings. Instead, the controllers will handle serialization manually using the two ObjectMapper instances.\n\n## 1. ArticlesResource.java -> ArticlesController.java\n\nConvert from JAX-RS to Spring MVC:\n- Replace `@Path` with `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")`\n- `@GET` -> `@GetMapping`, `@POST` -> `@PostMapping`, `@PUT` -> `@PutMapping`, `@DELETE` -> `@DeleteMapping`\n- `@PathParam` -> `@PathVariable`, `@QueryParam` -> `@RequestParam(required = false, defaultValue = \"\")`\n- `@Produces`/`@Consumes` -> handled by Spring\n- `@Context SecurityContext` -> Replace with custom: inject a `@RequestAttribute(required=false) UUID loggedUserId` parameter\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` -> Use constructor injection (use Lombok `@RequiredArgsConstructor` with `private final` fields)\n- Remove `@Transactional` from methods (will be handled at service/DAO level)\n- Return `ResponseEntity<String>` from methods that write JSON using ObjectMapper\n- Keep the two ObjectMapper instances: one regular `objectMapper` and one `noWrapObjectMapper`\n- The `@Secured` annotation will be replaced with `@Authenticated` (we'll define it) and `@Authenticated(optional=true)` for optional auth\n- Import from Spring packages instead of Jakarta\n\nHere's the exact pattern for the controller:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Authenticated;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.MediaType;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class ArticlesResource {\n\n    private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    private final CreateArticle createArticle;\n    private final FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    private final UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    private final DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    private final CreateComment createComment;\n    private final DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    private final FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    private final FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    private final UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    private final ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n\n    @GetMapping(value = \"/feed\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    @Authenticated\n    public ResponseEntity<String> feed(\n            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int offset,\n            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int limit,\n            @RequestAttribute(name = \"loggedUserId\", required = false) UUID loggedUserId) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        final var articlesFilter = new ArticleFilter(offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, null, null, null);\n        final var articlesPageResult = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter.handle(articlesFilter);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)));\n    }\n\n    // ... similar pattern for all other methods\n}\n```\n\nFor the `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` field, this MUST be annotated alongside the `final` declaration. The constructor will need both ObjectMapper beans injected.\n\nACTUALLY - due to how `@RequiredArgsConstructor` works with `@Qualifier`, we need a different approach. Instead, use explicit constructor:\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")\npublic class ArticlesResource {\n\n    private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    // ... all final fields ...\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    private final ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n\n    public ArticlesResource(\n            FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter,\n            // ... all params ...\n            ObjectMapper objectMapper,\n            @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper) {\n        this.findArticlesByFilter = findArticlesByFilter;\n        // ... assignments ...\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n        this.noWrapObjectMapper = noWrapObjectMapper;\n    }\n    \n    // methods...\n}\n```\n\nApply this same pattern to ALL resource/controller classes.\n\nFor `@Transactional` on methods - use `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional` instead of `jakarta.transaction.Transactional`.\n\nFor `@Valid` on request bodies - use `@Valid @RequestBody` together.\n\n## 2. UsersResource.java\n\nConvert similarly. The `create` method has `@Context SecurityException context` which should just be removed (it's not actually using SecurityContext, it's using SecurityException by mistake - just remove the parameter). The login method stays the same pattern.\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/users\")\npublic class UsersResource {\n    private final CreateUser createUser;\n    private final LoginUser loginUser;\n    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    // constructor...\n\n    @PostMapping(consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    @Transactional\n    public ResponseEntity<String> create(@Valid @RequestBody NewUserRequestWrapper newUserRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.getUser().toCreateUserInput());\n        final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new UserResponse(user, token)));\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(value = \"/login\", consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> login(@Valid @RequestBody LoginRequestWrapper loginRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        // ... same logic\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 3. UserResource.java\n\nSame pattern. For authenticated endpoints, add `@Authenticated` and use `@RequestAttribute(name = \"loggedUserId\", required = false) UUID loggedUserId` then do:\n```java\n@GetMapping(produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n@Authenticated\npublic ResponseEntity<String> getUser(@RequestAttribute(\"loggedUserId\") UUID loggedUserId) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    final var user = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n## 4. TagsResource.java\n\nSimple conversion - just RestController + GetMapping. No auth needed.\n\n## 5. ProfilesResource.java\n\nSame pattern as ArticlesResource with both authenticated and optional-auth endpoints.\n\n## 6. ResourceUtils.java\n\nChange from:\n- `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component` (or `@Service`)\n- `@Inject` -> constructor injection\n- `SecurityContext` parameter -> `UUID loggedUserId` parameter (it's already using UUID)\n\nKeep the same business logic. The method `getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext)` is no longer needed since we pass UUID directly. But keep it for compatibility if controllers still reference it - actually, remove it since controllers will pass UUID directly.\n\nWait, actually the ResourceUtils.getLoggedUserId is still used in controllers. Let me think about this differently.\n\nIn the Spring version, the authentication filter will set a request attribute `loggedUserId` (UUID), and controllers will receive it as `@RequestAttribute`. So ResourceUtils doesn't need `getLoggedUserId` anymore - controllers will just pass the UUID directly to `resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)`.\n\nSo modify ResourceUtils:\n- Remove `getLoggedUserId` method \n- Keep all other methods\n- Change to `@Service` with constructor injection\n\n## 7. Authentication Filter\n\nCreate a Spring HandlerInterceptor at:\n`src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/AuthenticationFilter.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n\nimport com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTVerificationException;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Authenticated;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.web.method.HandlerMethod;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.HandlerInterceptor;\n\n@Component\npublic class AuthenticationFilter implements HandlerInterceptor {\n\n    private static final String AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX = \"Token \";\n    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n\n    public AuthenticationFilter(TokenProvider tokenProvider) {\n        this.tokenProvider = tokenProvider;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean preHandle(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response, Object handler) throws Exception {\n        if (!(handler instanceof HandlerMethod handlerMethod)) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        \n        Authenticated methodAuth = handlerMethod.getMethodAnnotation(Authenticated.class);\n        Authenticated classAuth = handlerMethod.getBeanType().getAnnotation(Authenticated.class);\n        \n        // No auth annotation - allow through\n        if (methodAuth == null && classAuth == null) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        \n        boolean optional = methodAuth != null ? methodAuth.optional() : classAuth.optional();\n        \n        String authHeader = request.getHeader(\"Authorization\");\n        \n        if (authHeader != null && authHeader.startsWith(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX)) {\n            String token = authHeader.substring(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX.length());\n            try {\n                DecodedJWT decodedJWT = tokenProvider.verify(token);\n                request.setAttribute(\"loggedUserId\", java.util.UUID.fromString(decodedJWT.getSubject()));\n            } catch (JWTVerificationException ex) {\n                response.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_UNAUTHORIZED);\n                response.getWriter().write(\"{\\\"errors\\\":{\\\"body\\\":[\\\"Unauthorized\\\"]}}\");\n                return false;\n            }\n        } else if (!optional) {\n            response.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_UNAUTHORIZED);\n            response.setContentType(\"application/json\");\n            response.getWriter().write(\"{\\\"errors\\\":{\\\"body\\\":[\\\"Unauthorized\\\"]}}\");\n            return false;\n        }\n        \n        return true;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 8. Create the @Authenticated annotation\n\nCreate: `src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Authenticated.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\n\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface Authenticated {\n    boolean optional() default false;\n}\n```\n\n## 9. Create WebMvcConfig to register the interceptor\n\nCreate: `src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/config/WebMvcConfig.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.config;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter.AuthenticationFilter;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.CorsRegistry;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.InterceptorRegistry;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.WebMvcConfigurer;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class WebMvcConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {\n\n    private final AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter;\n\n    public WebMvcConfig(AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter) {\n        this.authenticationFilter = authenticationFilter;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void addInterceptors(InterceptorRegistry registry) {\n        registry.addInterceptor(authenticationFilter);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void addCorsMappings(CorsRegistry registry) {\n        registry.addMapping(\"/**\")\n                .allowedOrigins(\"*\")\n                .allowedMethods(\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\")\n                .allowedHeaders(\"*\")\n                .maxAge(3600);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 10. Delete the AuthorizationFilter.java (no longer needed - we handle roles via @Authenticated)\n\nThe authorization was based on Roles but in the original app, all authenticated users get USER role. So we simplify: if authenticated, you're authorized. Delete AuthorizationFilter.java.\n\n## 11. Delete the old @Secured annotation and the security context classes\n\nDelete:\n- `infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Secured.java` (replaced by @Authenticated)\n- `infrastructure/web/security/context/DecodedJWTSecurityContext.java` (no longer needed)\n- `infrastructure/web/security/context/EmptySecurityContext.java` (no longer needed)\n\n## 12. Keep the Role.java enum (no changes needed)\n\nNow please write ALL these files. For files that need to be deleted, write them as empty/stub files (or just don't touch them, we'll handle deletion separately).\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file before writing to it. For new files, just use Write. Write exact, complete, compilable Java code. Do NOT use placeholders or \"// ... similar\" patterns - write out every method completely.\n\nFor the controllers, here are the exact method signatures I need migrated:\n\n### ArticlesResource methods:\n1. feed - GET /feed - @Authenticated - returns articlesResponse via noWrapObjectMapper\n2. getArticles - GET / - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns articlesResponse via noWrapObjectMapper  \n3. create - POST / - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper, status CREATED\n4. findBySlug - GET /{slug} - no auth - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n5. update - PUT /{slug} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n6. delete - DELETE /{slug} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns ok\n7. getCommentsBySlug - GET /{slug}/comments - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns commentsResponse via noWrapObjectMapper\n8. createComment - POST /{slug}/comments - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns commentResponse via objectMapper\n9. deleteComment - DELETE /{slug}/comments/{id} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns ok\n10. favoriteArticle - POST /{slug}/favorite - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n11. unfavoriteArticle - DELETE /{slug}/favorite - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n\n### ProfilesResource methods:\n1. getProfile - GET /{username} - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n2. follow - POST /{username}/follow - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n3. unfollow - DELETE /{username}/follow - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n\nWrite all files now."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":621,"cache_read_input_tokens":130750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10510},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"55a8b891-3de3-4d4c-b845-47fcde4bc122"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CvdG2Rxx8HzcuJQZgJdFDx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor DAOs and domain layer","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version.\n\n## General migration rules for ALL files:\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` -> constructor injection (Spring autowiring)\n- `jakarta.inject.Singleton` -> `@Service` or `@Component` (from Spring)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` -> `@Service` or `@Component`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent` -> `@Service` or `@Component`\n- `jakarta.inject.Named` -> `@Component(\"name\")` or just remove if not needed\n- `jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext` -> `@PersistenceContext` (this stays the same - it's JPA standard, Spring supports it)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces` -> `@Bean` in a `@Configuration` class\n- Keep `jakarta.persistence.*` imports as-is (JPA annotations stay the same in Spring Boot 3.x)\n- Keep `jakarta.validation.*` imports as-is (Bean Validation annotations stay the same)\n- Use constructor injection with final fields everywhere\n\n## Files to rewrite:\n\n### 1. AbstractDAO.java\nPath: src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/AbstractDAO.java\n\nChange `@PersistenceContext` to still use `@PersistenceContext` (Spring supports it). But since abstract classes can't be auto-wired easily, use `@PersistenceContext protected EntityManager em;` which Spring will inject.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.persistence.Query;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.*;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\n\npublic abstract class AbstractDAO<ENTITY, ID> {\n\n    @PersistenceContext\n    protected EntityManager em;\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods exactly the same\n}\n```\n\nThis file actually barely changes - just verify the imports are fine.\n\n### 2. UserDAO.java\nChange from `@Singleton` to `@Repository` (Spring stereotype). Change `@Inject` to constructor injection.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.UserEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n\n// ... same imports\n\n@Repository\npublic class UserDAO extends AbstractDAO<UserEntity, UUID> implements UserRepository {\n\n    private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n    public UserDAO(EntityUtils entityUtils) {\n        this.entityUtils = entityUtils;\n    }\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods exactly the same\n}\n```\n\n### 3. ArticleDAO.java\nSame pattern - `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 4. TagDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 5. CommentDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 6. TagRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 7. FollowRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 8. FavoriteRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 9. EntityUtils.java\n`@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`. Change `@Inject @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")` to constructor injection with `@Qualifier(\"usermodelbuilder\")`.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class EntityUtils {\n\n    private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n\n    public EntityUtils(\n            @Qualifier(\"usermodelbuilder\") UserModelBuilder userBuilder,\n            TagBuilder tagBuilder,\n            ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder,\n            CommentBuilder commentBuilder) {\n        this.userBuilder = userBuilder;\n        this.tagBuilder = tagBuilder;\n        this.articleBuilder = articleBuilder;\n        this.commentBuilder = commentBuilder;\n    }\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods the same\n}\n```\n\n### 10-13. Entity files (UserEntity, ArticleEntity, CommentEntity, TagEntity, TagRelationshipEntity, FollowRelationshipEntity, FavoriteRelationshipEntity)\nThese use `jakarta.persistence.*` annotations which are KEPT AS-IS in Spring Boot 3.x. The `org.hibernate.annotations` are also kept. So these files need NO CHANGES. But just to be safe, read and verify each one.\n\n### 14. SimpleQueryBuilder.java\nNo changes needed - it's a plain utility class.\n\n### 15-38. ALL domain feature implementation files\nThese all follow the same pattern. Change:\n- `@Singleton` or `@Dependent` -> `@Service`\n- `@Inject private X x;` -> constructor injection with `private final X x;`\n\nApply this to ALL files in `domain/feature/impl/`:\n- CreateUserImpl.java\n- LoginUserImpl.java\n- CreateArticleImpl.java\n- UpdateArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- DeleteArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- FindUserByIdImpl.java\n- FindUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- UpdateUserImpl.java\n- FindArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- FindArticleByIdImpl.java\n- FindArticleByAuthorAndSlugImpl.java\n- FindArticlesByFilterImpl.java\n- FindMostRecentArticlesByFilterImpl.java\n- CreateCommentImpl.java\n- DeleteCommentImpl.java\n- FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl.java\n- FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl.java\n- FavoriteArticleImpl.java\n- UnfavoriteArticleImpl.java\n- ArticleFavoritesCountImpl.java\n- IsArticleFavoritedImpl.java\n- FollowUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- IsFollowingUserImpl.java\n- CreateTagImpl.java\n- FindTagsImpl.java\n- FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl.java\n- FindArticleTagsImpl.java\n- CreateSlugByTitleImpl.java\n\n### 39. ModelValidator.java\nChange `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, `@Inject` -> constructor injection.\n\n### 40-42. Domain Model Builders\n- UserModelBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")` -> `@Component(\"usermodelbuilder\")`, constructor injection for ModelValidator\n- ArticleModelBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection  \n- CommentBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection\n- TagBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection\n\n### 43-45. Infrastructure Providers\n- JwtTokenProvider.java: Change `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`. Change `@ConfigProperty(name=\"...\")` -> `@Value(\"${...}\")`. Keep the constructor injection pattern but use `@Value` annotations.\n- BCryptHashProvider.java: `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`\n- SlugifySlugProvider.java: `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`, remove `@Inject` from constructor (Spring will auto-call it)\n\n### 46. SerializerConfig.java\nConvert from CDI producer to Spring `@Configuration` with `@Bean` methods:\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Primary;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class SerializerConfig {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read EACH file first, then write the migrated version. Write COMPLETE files, no placeholders. Write ALL files listed above."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":621,"cache_read_input_tokens":130750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10510},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"92400178-b6e6-441b-89ee-bbaadad68cf1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CvdG2Rxx8HzcuJQZgJdFDx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_015RrdjQQEmREeaPUfcJZvL7","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor exception mappers and models","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version.\n\n## 1. Convert Exception Mappers to @ControllerAdvice\n\nThe three JAX-RS ExceptionMapper classes need to become a single `@RestControllerAdvice` class.\n\nDelete or overwrite: \n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java`\n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java`\n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java`\n\nCreate a single file: `infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.ForbiddenException;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.http.converter.HttpMessageNotReadableException;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.MethodArgumentNotValidException;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ExceptionHandler;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestControllerAdvice;\n\n@RestControllerAdvice\npublic class GlobalExceptionHandler {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    public GlobalExceptionHandler(ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UnauthorizedException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUnauthorized(UnauthorizedException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED.toString())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ForbiddenException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleForbidden(ForbiddenException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN.toString())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UserNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUserNotFound(UserNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ArticleNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleArticleNotFound(ArticleNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(TagNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleTagNotFound(TagNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(CommentNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleCommentNotFound(CommentNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(EmailAlreadyExistsException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleEmailExists(EmailAlreadyExistsException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UsernameAlreadyExistsException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUsernameExists(UsernameAlreadyExistsException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(InvalidPasswordException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleInvalidPassword(InvalidPasswordException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ModelValidationException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleModelValidation(ModelValidationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ConstraintViolationException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleConstraintViolation(ConstraintViolationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n        ex.getConstraintViolations().forEach(cv -> errorResponse.getBody().add(cv.getMessage()));\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleMethodArgumentNotValid(MethodArgumentNotValidException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n        ex.getBindingResult().getAllErrors().forEach(error -> errorResponse.getBody().add(error.getDefaultMessage()));\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(HttpMessageNotReadableException.class) \n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleHttpMessageNotReadable(HttpMessageNotReadableException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(\"request body must be not null\")));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 2. Update Request Model classes\n\nThese classes use `jakarta.validation.*` which stays the same in Spring Boot 3. BUT some use `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` which is a JSON-B annotation not available in Spring. Remove that import.\n\nFiles to update (read each first, then write):\n\n### NewArticleRequest.java\nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\n### UpdateArticleRequest.java  \nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\n### NewCommentRequest.java\nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\nFor the request WRAPPER classes, check if they need `@JsonRootName` to handle the wrapping. Since the API receives payloads like `{\"user\": {...}}`, `{\"article\": {...}}` etc., and we have UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled on the primary ObjectMapper, the wrappers should handle this automatically via Jackson.\n\nWait - actually the wrappers DON'T use `@JsonRootName`. The wrapping is handled by the wrapper classes themselves (e.g., `NewUserRequestWrapper` has a field `user` of type `NewUserRequest`). This means they DON'T need UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE - they use explicit wrapper objects.\n\nSo the request body deserialization will work fine WITHOUT UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE because the wrapper classes themselves represent the outer JSON structure.\n\nBUT - for the primary ObjectMapper (used for responses), WRAP_ROOT_VALUE is enabled which adds a root wrapper based on `@JsonRootName`. The responses use `@JsonRootName(\"user\")`, `@JsonRootName(\"article\")` etc.\n\nSo actually for Spring Boot, the primary ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled would cause issues with deserializing request bodies (it would try to UNWRAP them looking for root names).\n\nSOLUTION: We need the primary ObjectMapper to NOT have WRAP_ROOT_VALUE. The controllers that need wrapping use the primary objectMapper (which has WRAP_ROOT_VALUE for responses only). But Spring's message converter uses it for request deserialization too.\n\nBetter approach: Make the PRIMARY ObjectMapper (used by Spring MVC for request/response) a PLAIN one. Then keep two named beans for manual serialization in controllers:\n\nIn `SerializerConfig.java`:\n```java\n@Configuration\npublic class SerializerConfig {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n        // Primary ObjectMapper used by Spring MVC - NO root wrapping\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper wrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThen in controllers:\n- Where the original used `objectMapper` (wrapping mapper) -> use `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`\n- Where the original used `noWrapObjectMapper` -> use `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`\n\nActually wait - looking at the original code more carefully:\n\nThe ORIGINAL SerializerConfig creates:\n1. Default ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE (used for single-entity responses like article, user, comment, profile)\n2. NoWrapRootValue ObjectMapper (used for list responses like articles, comments)\n\nIn controllers:\n- `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` - wraps root value (adds `{\"article\": {...}}`)\n- `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` - no wrapping (returns raw `{\"articles\": [...], \"articlesCount\": 5}`)\n\nFor request body deserialization, Spring MVC will use the primary ObjectMapper. Since request bodies come as wrappers (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}`), and the wrapper classes like `NewUserRequestWrapper` have a `user` field - this works WITHOUT UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE because the wrapper class IS the JSON structure.\n\nSo the correct approach:\n1. Primary ObjectMapper (for Spring MVC request deserialization): PLAIN, no wrapping\n2. \"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\" bean: for controller response serialization with root wrapping\n3. \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\" bean: for controller response serialization without wrapping\n\nIMPORTANT: Tell the other agent working on controllers that:\n- Original `objectMapper` (with wrapping) -> inject `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper`  \n- Original `noWrapObjectMapper` (no wrapping) -> inject `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper`\n\nNow please write the files:\n\n1. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java` as shown above (BUT use the primary ObjectMapper which is plain - error responses don't need wrapping... wait, in the original they used the wrapping ObjectMapper for errors too, and ErrorResponse has `@JsonRootName(\"errors\")`. So use `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` in the GlobalExceptionHandler.\n\n2. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java` as an EMPTY placeholder (or delete content):\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n// This class has been replaced by GlobalExceptionHandler\n```\n\n3. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java` similarly empty.\n\n4. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java` similarly empty.\n\n5. Update `infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java` with the three-bean approach shown above.\n\n6. Update `NewArticleRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import\n7. Update `UpdateArticleRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import  \n8. Update `NewCommentRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import\n\n9. Update `infrastructure/web/qualifiers/NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper.java`:\nThe CDI qualifier is no longer needed. Replace with empty/unused class:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers;\n// No longer needed in Spring Boot - using @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") instead\n```\n\n10. The validation constraint and validator files (`AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull.java` and `AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator.java`) use `jakarta.validation.*` which is still valid in Spring Boot 3. No changes needed, but verify.\n\n11. Exception classes (UnauthorizedException, ForbiddenException, InfrastructureException) - no changes needed, verify.\n\nRead each file first, then write ALL files."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":621,"cache_read_input_tokens":130750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10510},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"17f8526b-d401-413d-bbf3-83d2865044a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version. \n\nCRITICAL: The API currently uses a wrapper pattern for request bodies (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}` wrapping) and a `@JsonRootName` pattern for responses. The wrapping/unwrapping in the original Jakarta version is done via two ObjectMapper beans - one with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled and one without. In Spring Boot, we will NOT use the global Jackson WRAP_ROOT_VALUE settings. Instead, the controllers will handle serialization manually using the two ObjectMapper instances.\n\n## 1. ArticlesResource.java -> ArticlesController.java\n\nConvert from JAX-RS to Spring MVC:\n- Replace `@Path` with `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")`\n- `@GET` -> `@GetMapping`, `@POST` -> `@PostMapping`, `@PUT` -> `@PutMapping`, `@DELETE` -> `@DeleteMapping`\n- `@PathParam` -> `@PathVariable`, `@QueryParam` -> `@RequestParam(required = false, defaultValue = \"\")`\n- `@Produces`/`@Consumes` -> handled by Spring\n- `@Context SecurityContext` -> Replace with custom: inject a `@RequestAttribute(required=false) UUID loggedUserId` parameter\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` -> Use constructor injection (use Lombok `@RequiredArgsConstructor` with `private final` fields)\n- Remove `@Transactional` from methods (will be handled at service/DAO level)\n- Return `ResponseEntity<String>` from methods that write JSON using ObjectMapper\n- Keep the two ObjectMapper instances: one regular `objectMapper` and one `noWrapObjectMapper`\n- The `@Secured` annotation will be replaced with `@Authenticated` (we'll define it) and `@Authenticated(optional=true)` for optional auth\n- Import from Spring packages instead of Jakarta\n\nHere's the exact pattern for the controller:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Authenticated;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.MediaType;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class ArticlesResource {\n\n    private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    private final CreateArticle createArticle;\n    private final FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    private final UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    private final DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    private final CreateComment createComment;\n    private final DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    private final FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    private final FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    private final UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    private final ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n\n    @GetMapping(value = \"/feed\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    @Authenticated\n    public ResponseEntity<String> feed(\n            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int offset,\n            @RequestParam(defaultValue = \"0\") int limit,\n            @RequestAttribute(name = \"loggedUserId\", required = false) UUID loggedUserId) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        final var articlesFilter = new ArticleFilter(offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, null, null, null);\n        final var articlesPageResult = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter.handle(articlesFilter);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)));\n    }\n\n    // ... similar pattern for all other methods\n}\n```\n\nFor the `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` field, this MUST be annotated alongside the `final` declaration. The constructor will need both ObjectMapper beans injected.\n\nACTUALLY - due to how `@RequiredArgsConstructor` works with `@Qualifier`, we need a different approach. Instead, use explicit constructor:\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")\npublic class ArticlesResource {\n\n    private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    // ... all final fields ...\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    private final ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n\n    public ArticlesResource(\n            FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter,\n            // ... all params ...\n            ObjectMapper objectMapper,\n            @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper) {\n        this.findArticlesByFilter = findArticlesByFilter;\n        // ... assignments ...\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n        this.noWrapObjectMapper = noWrapObjectMapper;\n    }\n    \n    // methods...\n}\n```\n\nApply this same pattern to ALL resource/controller classes.\n\nFor `@Transactional` on methods - use `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional` instead of `jakarta.transaction.Transactional`.\n\nFor `@Valid` on request bodies - use `@Valid @RequestBody` together.\n\n## 2. UsersResource.java\n\nConvert similarly. The `create` method has `@Context SecurityException context` which should just be removed (it's not actually using SecurityContext, it's using SecurityException by mistake - just remove the parameter). The login method stays the same pattern.\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/users\")\npublic class UsersResource {\n    private final CreateUser createUser;\n    private final LoginUser loginUser;\n    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    // constructor...\n\n    @PostMapping(consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    @Transactional\n    public ResponseEntity<String> create(@Valid @RequestBody NewUserRequestWrapper newUserRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.getUser().toCreateUserInput());\n        final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new UserResponse(user, token)));\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(value = \"/login\", consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> login(@Valid @RequestBody LoginRequestWrapper loginRequest) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        // ... same logic\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 3. UserResource.java\n\nSame pattern. For authenticated endpoints, add `@Authenticated` and use `@RequestAttribute(name = \"loggedUserId\", required = false) UUID loggedUserId` then do:\n```java\n@GetMapping(produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n@Authenticated\npublic ResponseEntity<String> getUser(@RequestAttribute(\"loggedUserId\") UUID loggedUserId) throws JsonProcessingException {\n    final var user = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n## 4. TagsResource.java\n\nSimple conversion - just RestController + GetMapping. No auth needed.\n\n## 5. ProfilesResource.java\n\nSame pattern as ArticlesResource with both authenticated and optional-auth endpoints.\n\n## 6. ResourceUtils.java\n\nChange from:\n- `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component` (or `@Service`)\n- `@Inject` -> constructor injection\n- `SecurityContext` parameter -> `UUID loggedUserId` parameter (it's already using UUID)\n\nKeep the same business logic. The method `getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext)` is no longer needed since we pass UUID directly. But keep it for compatibility if controllers still reference it - actually, remove it since controllers will pass UUID directly.\n\nWait, actually the ResourceUtils.getLoggedUserId is still used in controllers. Let me think about this differently.\n\nIn the Spring version, the authentication filter will set a request attribute `loggedUserId` (UUID), and controllers will receive it as `@RequestAttribute`. So ResourceUtils doesn't need `getLoggedUserId` anymore - controllers will just pass the UUID directly to `resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)`.\n\nSo modify ResourceUtils:\n- Remove `getLoggedUserId` method \n- Keep all other methods\n- Change to `@Service` with constructor injection\n\n## 7. Authentication Filter\n\nCreate a Spring HandlerInterceptor at:\n`src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/AuthenticationFilter.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n\nimport com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTVerificationException;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Authenticated;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.web.method.HandlerMethod;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.HandlerInterceptor;\n\n@Component\npublic class AuthenticationFilter implements HandlerInterceptor {\n\n    private static final String AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX = \"Token \";\n    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n\n    public AuthenticationFilter(TokenProvider tokenProvider) {\n        this.tokenProvider = tokenProvider;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean preHandle(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response, Object handler) throws Exception {\n        if (!(handler instanceof HandlerMethod handlerMethod)) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        \n        Authenticated methodAuth = handlerMethod.getMethodAnnotation(Authenticated.class);\n        Authenticated classAuth = handlerMethod.getBeanType().getAnnotation(Authenticated.class);\n        \n        // No auth annotation - allow through\n        if (methodAuth == null && classAuth == null) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        \n        boolean optional = methodAuth != null ? methodAuth.optional() : classAuth.optional();\n        \n        String authHeader = request.getHeader(\"Authorization\");\n        \n        if (authHeader != null && authHeader.startsWith(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX)) {\n            String token = authHeader.substring(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX.length());\n            try {\n                DecodedJWT decodedJWT = tokenProvider.verify(token);\n                request.setAttribute(\"loggedUserId\", java.util.UUID.fromString(decodedJWT.getSubject()));\n            } catch (JWTVerificationException ex) {\n                response.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_UNAUTHORIZED);\n                response.getWriter().write(\"{\\\"errors\\\":{\\\"body\\\":[\\\"Unauthorized\\\"]}}\");\n                return false;\n            }\n        } else if (!optional) {\n            response.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_UNAUTHORIZED);\n            response.setContentType(\"application/json\");\n            response.getWriter().write(\"{\\\"errors\\\":{\\\"body\\\":[\\\"Unauthorized\\\"]}}\");\n            return false;\n        }\n        \n        return true;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 8. Create the @Authenticated annotation\n\nCreate: `src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Authenticated.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\n\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface Authenticated {\n    boolean optional() default false;\n}\n```\n\n## 9. Create WebMvcConfig to register the interceptor\n\nCreate: `src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/config/WebMvcConfig.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.config;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter.AuthenticationFilter;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.CorsRegistry;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.InterceptorRegistry;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.WebMvcConfigurer;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class WebMvcConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {\n\n    private final AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter;\n\n    public WebMvcConfig(AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter) {\n        this.authenticationFilter = authenticationFilter;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void addInterceptors(InterceptorRegistry registry) {\n        registry.addInterceptor(authenticationFilter);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void addCorsMappings(CorsRegistry registry) {\n        registry.addMapping(\"/**\")\n                .allowedOrigins(\"*\")\n                .allowedMethods(\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\")\n                .allowedHeaders(\"*\")\n                .maxAge(3600);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 10. Delete the AuthorizationFilter.java (no longer needed - we handle roles via @Authenticated)\n\nThe authorization was based on Roles but in the original app, all authenticated users get USER role. So we simplify: if authenticated, you're authorized. Delete AuthorizationFilter.java.\n\n## 11. Delete the old @Secured annotation and the security context classes\n\nDelete:\n- `infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Secured.java` (replaced by @Authenticated)\n- `infrastructure/web/security/context/DecodedJWTSecurityContext.java` (no longer needed)\n- `infrastructure/web/security/context/EmptySecurityContext.java` (no longer needed)\n\n## 12. Keep the Role.java enum (no changes needed)\n\nNow please write ALL these files. For files that need to be deleted, write them as empty/stub files (or just don't touch them, we'll handle deletion separately).\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file before writing to it. For new files, just use Write. Write exact, complete, compilable Java code. Do NOT use placeholders or \"// ... similar\" patterns - write out every method completely.\n\nFor the controllers, here are the exact method signatures I need migrated:\n\n### ArticlesResource methods:\n1. feed - GET /feed - @Authenticated - returns articlesResponse via noWrapObjectMapper\n2. getArticles - GET / - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns articlesResponse via noWrapObjectMapper  \n3. create - POST / - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper, status CREATED\n4. findBySlug - GET /{slug} - no auth - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n5. update - PUT /{slug} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n6. delete - DELETE /{slug} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns ok\n7. getCommentsBySlug - GET /{slug}/comments - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns commentsResponse via noWrapObjectMapper\n8. createComment - POST /{slug}/comments - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns commentResponse via objectMapper\n9. deleteComment - DELETE /{slug}/comments/{id} - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns ok\n10. favoriteArticle - POST /{slug}/favorite - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n11. unfavoriteArticle - DELETE /{slug}/favorite - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns articleResponse via objectMapper\n\n### ProfilesResource methods:\n1. getProfile - GET /{username} - @Authenticated(optional=true) - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n2. follow - POST /{username}/follow - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n3. unfollow - DELETE /{username}/follow - @Authenticated @Transactional - returns profileResponse via objectMapper\n\nWrite all files now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Eh4ku11KtkK62EAjxkMd6v","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"55ce8317-0227-4466-8c93-c209277baade"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version.\n\n## General migration rules for ALL files:\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` -> constructor injection (Spring autowiring)\n- `jakarta.inject.Singleton` -> `@Service` or `@Component` (from Spring)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` -> `@Service` or `@Component`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent` -> `@Service` or `@Component`\n- `jakarta.inject.Named` -> `@Component(\"name\")` or just remove if not needed\n- `jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext` -> `@PersistenceContext` (this stays the same - it's JPA standard, Spring supports it)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces` -> `@Bean` in a `@Configuration` class\n- Keep `jakarta.persistence.*` imports as-is (JPA annotations stay the same in Spring Boot 3.x)\n- Keep `jakarta.validation.*` imports as-is (Bean Validation annotations stay the same)\n- Use constructor injection with final fields everywhere\n\n## Files to rewrite:\n\n### 1. AbstractDAO.java\nPath: src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/AbstractDAO.java\n\nChange `@PersistenceContext` to still use `@PersistenceContext` (Spring supports it). But since abstract classes can't be auto-wired easily, use `@PersistenceContext protected EntityManager em;` which Spring will inject.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.persistence.Query;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.*;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\n\npublic abstract class AbstractDAO<ENTITY, ID> {\n\n    @PersistenceContext\n    protected EntityManager em;\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods exactly the same\n}\n```\n\nThis file actually barely changes - just verify the imports are fine.\n\n### 2. UserDAO.java\nChange from `@Singleton` to `@Repository` (Spring stereotype). Change `@Inject` to constructor injection.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.UserEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n\n// ... same imports\n\n@Repository\npublic class UserDAO extends AbstractDAO<UserEntity, UUID> implements UserRepository {\n\n    private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n    public UserDAO(EntityUtils entityUtils) {\n        this.entityUtils = entityUtils;\n    }\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods exactly the same\n}\n```\n\n### 3. ArticleDAO.java\nSame pattern - `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 4. TagDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 5. CommentDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 6. TagRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 7. FollowRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 8. FavoriteRelationshipDAO.java\n`@Dependent` -> `@Repository`, constructor injection.\n\n### 9. EntityUtils.java\n`@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`. Change `@Inject @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")` to constructor injection with `@Qualifier(\"usermodelbuilder\")`.\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class EntityUtils {\n\n    private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n\n    public EntityUtils(\n            @Qualifier(\"usermodelbuilder\") UserModelBuilder userBuilder,\n            TagBuilder tagBuilder,\n            ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder,\n            CommentBuilder commentBuilder) {\n        this.userBuilder = userBuilder;\n        this.tagBuilder = tagBuilder;\n        this.articleBuilder = articleBuilder;\n        this.commentBuilder = commentBuilder;\n    }\n\n    // ... keep all existing methods the same\n}\n```\n\n### 10-13. Entity files (UserEntity, ArticleEntity, CommentEntity, TagEntity, TagRelationshipEntity, FollowRelationshipEntity, FavoriteRelationshipEntity)\nThese use `jakarta.persistence.*` annotations which are KEPT AS-IS in Spring Boot 3.x. The `org.hibernate.annotations` are also kept. So these files need NO CHANGES. But just to be safe, read and verify each one.\n\n### 14. SimpleQueryBuilder.java\nNo changes needed - it's a plain utility class.\n\n### 15-38. ALL domain feature implementation files\nThese all follow the same pattern. Change:\n- `@Singleton` or `@Dependent` -> `@Service`\n- `@Inject private X x;` -> constructor injection with `private final X x;`\n\nApply this to ALL files in `domain/feature/impl/`:\n- CreateUserImpl.java\n- LoginUserImpl.java\n- CreateArticleImpl.java\n- UpdateArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- DeleteArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- FindUserByIdImpl.java\n- FindUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- UpdateUserImpl.java\n- FindArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- FindArticleByIdImpl.java\n- FindArticleByAuthorAndSlugImpl.java\n- FindArticlesByFilterImpl.java\n- FindMostRecentArticlesByFilterImpl.java\n- CreateCommentImpl.java\n- DeleteCommentImpl.java\n- FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl.java\n- FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl.java\n- FavoriteArticleImpl.java\n- UnfavoriteArticleImpl.java\n- ArticleFavoritesCountImpl.java\n- IsArticleFavoritedImpl.java\n- FollowUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl.java\n- IsFollowingUserImpl.java\n- CreateTagImpl.java\n- FindTagsImpl.java\n- FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl.java\n- FindArticleTagsImpl.java\n- CreateSlugByTitleImpl.java\n\n### 39. ModelValidator.java\nChange `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, `@Inject` -> constructor injection.\n\n### 40-42. Domain Model Builders\n- UserModelBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")` -> `@Component(\"usermodelbuilder\")`, constructor injection for ModelValidator\n- ArticleModelBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection  \n- CommentBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection\n- TagBuilder.java: Change `@Singleton` -> `@Component`, constructor injection\n\n### 43-45. Infrastructure Providers\n- JwtTokenProvider.java: Change `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`. Change `@ConfigProperty(name=\"...\")` -> `@Value(\"${...}\")`. Keep the constructor injection pattern but use `@Value` annotations.\n- BCryptHashProvider.java: `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`\n- SlugifySlugProvider.java: `@ApplicationScoped` -> `@Component`, remove `@Inject` from constructor (Spring will auto-call it)\n\n### 46. SerializerConfig.java\nConvert from CDI producer to Spring `@Configuration` with `@Bean` methods:\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Primary;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class SerializerConfig {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read EACH file first, then write the migrated version. Write COMPLETE files, no placeholders. Write ALL files listed above."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"8b2638b8-c4a8-4db4-8d28-f9b97e16e99d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE (MicroProfile/OpenLiberty) RealWorld API to Spring Boot. The project root is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nI need you to REWRITE the following files. Read each file first, then write the migrated version.\n\n## 1. Convert Exception Mappers to @ControllerAdvice\n\nThe three JAX-RS ExceptionMapper classes need to become a single `@RestControllerAdvice` class.\n\nDelete or overwrite: \n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java`\n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java`\n- `infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java`\n\nCreate a single file: `infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.ForbiddenException;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.http.converter.HttpMessageNotReadableException;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.MethodArgumentNotValidException;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ExceptionHandler;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestControllerAdvice;\n\n@RestControllerAdvice\npublic class GlobalExceptionHandler {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    public GlobalExceptionHandler(ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UnauthorizedException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUnauthorized(UnauthorizedException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED.toString())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ForbiddenException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleForbidden(ForbiddenException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN.toString())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UserNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUserNotFound(UserNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ArticleNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleArticleNotFound(ArticleNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(TagNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleTagNotFound(TagNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(CommentNotFoundException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleCommentNotFound(CommentNotFoundException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(EmailAlreadyExistsException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleEmailExists(EmailAlreadyExistsException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(UsernameAlreadyExistsException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleUsernameExists(UsernameAlreadyExistsException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CONFLICT)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(InvalidPasswordException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleInvalidPassword(InvalidPasswordException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ModelValidationException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleModelValidation(ModelValidationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessages())));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ConstraintViolationException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleConstraintViolation(ConstraintViolationException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n        ex.getConstraintViolations().forEach(cv -> errorResponse.getBody().add(cv.getMessage()));\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleMethodArgumentNotValid(MethodArgumentNotValidException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n        ex.getBindingResult().getAllErrors().forEach(error -> errorResponse.getBody().add(error.getDefaultMessage()));\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(HttpMessageNotReadableException.class) \n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleHttpMessageNotReadable(HttpMessageNotReadableException ex) throws JsonProcessingException {\n        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY)\n                .body(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ErrorResponse(\"request body must be not null\")));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 2. Update Request Model classes\n\nThese classes use `jakarta.validation.*` which stays the same in Spring Boot 3. BUT some use `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` which is a JSON-B annotation not available in Spring. Remove that import.\n\nFiles to update (read each first, then write):\n\n### NewArticleRequest.java\nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\n### UpdateArticleRequest.java  \nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\n### NewCommentRequest.java\nRemove `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` (not used but imported)\n\nFor the request WRAPPER classes, check if they need `@JsonRootName` to handle the wrapping. Since the API receives payloads like `{\"user\": {...}}`, `{\"article\": {...}}` etc., and we have UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled on the primary ObjectMapper, the wrappers should handle this automatically via Jackson.\n\nWait - actually the wrappers DON'T use `@JsonRootName`. The wrapping is handled by the wrapper classes themselves (e.g., `NewUserRequestWrapper` has a field `user` of type `NewUserRequest`). This means they DON'T need UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE - they use explicit wrapper objects.\n\nSo the request body deserialization will work fine WITHOUT UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE because the wrapper classes themselves represent the outer JSON structure.\n\nBUT - for the primary ObjectMapper (used for responses), WRAP_ROOT_VALUE is enabled which adds a root wrapper based on `@JsonRootName`. The responses use `@JsonRootName(\"user\")`, `@JsonRootName(\"article\")` etc.\n\nSo actually for Spring Boot, the primary ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled would cause issues with deserializing request bodies (it would try to UNWRAP them looking for root names).\n\nSOLUTION: We need the primary ObjectMapper to NOT have WRAP_ROOT_VALUE. The controllers that need wrapping use the primary objectMapper (which has WRAP_ROOT_VALUE for responses only). But Spring's message converter uses it for request deserialization too.\n\nBetter approach: Make the PRIMARY ObjectMapper (used by Spring MVC for request/response) a PLAIN one. Then keep two named beans for manual serialization in controllers:\n\nIn `SerializerConfig.java`:\n```java\n@Configuration\npublic class SerializerConfig {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Primary\n    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n        // Primary ObjectMapper used by Spring MVC - NO root wrapping\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper wrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n        return objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    @Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")\n    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThen in controllers:\n- Where the original used `objectMapper` (wrapping mapper) -> use `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`\n- Where the original used `noWrapObjectMapper` -> use `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`\n\nActually wait - looking at the original code more carefully:\n\nThe ORIGINAL SerializerConfig creates:\n1. Default ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE (used for single-entity responses like article, user, comment, profile)\n2. NoWrapRootValue ObjectMapper (used for list responses like articles, comments)\n\nIn controllers:\n- `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` - wraps root value (adds `{\"article\": {...}}`)\n- `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` - no wrapping (returns raw `{\"articles\": [...], \"articlesCount\": 5}`)\n\nFor request body deserialization, Spring MVC will use the primary ObjectMapper. Since request bodies come as wrappers (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}`), and the wrapper classes like `NewUserRequestWrapper` have a `user` field - this works WITHOUT UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE because the wrapper class IS the JSON structure.\n\nSo the correct approach:\n1. Primary ObjectMapper (for Spring MVC request deserialization): PLAIN, no wrapping\n2. \"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\" bean: for controller response serialization with root wrapping\n3. \"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\" bean: for controller response serialization without wrapping\n\nIMPORTANT: Tell the other agent working on controllers that:\n- Original `objectMapper` (with wrapping) -> inject `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper`  \n- Original `noWrapObjectMapper` (no wrapping) -> inject `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper`\n\nNow please write the files:\n\n1. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java` as shown above (BUT use the primary ObjectMapper which is plain - error responses don't need wrapping... wait, in the original they used the wrapping ObjectMapper for errors too, and ErrorResponse has `@JsonRootName(\"errors\")`. So use `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` in the GlobalExceptionHandler.\n\n2. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java` as an EMPTY placeholder (or delete content):\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n// This class has been replaced by GlobalExceptionHandler\n```\n\n3. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java` similarly empty.\n\n4. Write `infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java` similarly empty.\n\n5. Update `infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java` with the three-bean approach shown above.\n\n6. Update `NewArticleRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import\n7. Update `UpdateArticleRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import  \n8. Update `NewCommentRequest.java` - remove `jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable` import\n\n9. Update `infrastructure/web/qualifiers/NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper.java`:\nThe CDI qualifier is no longer needed. Replace with empty/unused class:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers;\n// No longer needed in Spring Boot - using @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") instead\n```\n\n10. The validation constraint and validator files (`AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull.java` and `AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator.java`) use `jakarta.validation.*` which is still valid in Spring Boot 3. No changes needed, but verify.\n\n11. Exception classes (UnauthorizedException, ForbiddenException, InfrastructureException) - no changes needed, verify.\n\nRead each file first, then write ALL files."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015RrdjQQEmREeaPUfcJZvL7","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"ad75fe8f-11a9-4467-8697-8f532b859c82"}
