{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012uD2y5jYZTrrxam4v9aDb6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    22→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    23→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    24→        favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"ad54aaf6-cbb2-4495-855b-ab0c5f02dfa7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EbE616rMaUQjnTmjLjrVzy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n    22→        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"67189001-d1bc-42cd-b85c-696425a76c29"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011VfkXqtskVwuE5RNwDNWLx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsArticleFavorited;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class IsArticleFavoritedImpl implements IsArticleFavorited {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public boolean handle(Article article, UUID currentUserId) {\n    19→        return favoriteRelationshipRepository.isFavorited(article, currentUserId);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"ba95af0c-f1f8-41fd-8862-83e9757ad896"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XzaUmmNS2BSxswQ57p3LGS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.UUID;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class FollowUserByUsernameImpl implements FollowUserByUsername {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    private FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public FollowRelationship handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    25→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    26→        final var userToFollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    27→        final var followingRelationship = new FollowRelationship(loggedUser, userToFollow);\n    28→        usersFollowedRepository.save(followingRelationship);\n    29→        return followingRelationship;\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_