{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Eh4ku11KtkK62EAjxkMd6v","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All the files have been successfully migrated. Let me create a summary of what was done:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated all the JAX-RS resource files to Spring MVC controllers. Here's what was completed:\n\n### Controllers Migrated (5 files)\n\n1. **ArticlesResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java`)\n   - Converted from `@Path` to `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")`\n   - All 11 methods migrated: feed, getArticles, create, findBySlug, update, delete, getCommentsBySlug, createComment, deleteComment, favoriteArticle, unfavoriteArticle\n   - Uses explicit constructor injection with `@Qualifier` for `noWrapObjectMapper`\n   - Returns `ResponseEntity<String>` for JSON responses (using ObjectMapper manually)\n   - Proper `@Authenticated` and `@Authenticated(optional=true)` annotations applied\n\n2. **UsersResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java`)\n   - Converted to Spring MVC with `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/users\")`\n   - Removed the erroneous `@Context SecurityException` parameter from create method\n   - Both methods (create, login) working with proper exception handling\n\n3. **UserResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`)\n   - Converted to Spring MVC with `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/user\")`\n   - Both methods (getUser, update) use `@RequestAttribute(\"loggedUserId\")` for authentication\n   - Applied `@Authenticated` annotation\n\n4. **TagsResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java`)\n   - Simple conversion to Spring MVC\n   - No authentication required\n   - Returns `ResponseEntity<TagsResponse>` directly (not using ObjectMapper since TagsResponse is auto-serialized)\n\n5. **ProfilesResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`)\n   - All 3 methods migrated: getProfile, follow, unfollow\n   - Proper mix of `@Authenticated` and `@Authenticated(optional=true)`\n   - Returns JSON via ObjectMapper\n\n### Utility Class Updated\n\n6. **ResourceUtils.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java`)\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Service`\n   - Removed `getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext)` method (no longer needed)\n   - Uses constructor injection\n   - Controllers now pass UUID directly instead of SecurityContext\n\n### New Security Infrastructure (3 files)\n\n7. **@Authenticated Annotation** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Authenticated.java`)\n   - Replaces the old `@Secured` annotation\n   - Supports `optional = true` parameter for optional authentication\n   - Runtime retention, applicable to types and methods\n\n8. **AuthenticationFilter** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/filter/AuthenticationFilter.java`)\n   - Spring `HandlerInterceptor` implementation\n   - Checks for `@Authenticated` annotation on methods/classes\n   - Validates JWT tokens with \"Token \" prefix\n   - Sets `loggedUserId` request attribute on successful authentication\n   - Returns 401 with proper JSON error response for unauthorized requests\n\n9. **WebMvcConfig** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/config/WebMvcConfig.java`)\n   - Registers the AuthenticationFilter interceptor\n   - Configures CORS to allow all origins, common HTTP methods, and all headers\n\n### Key Migration Patterns Applied\n\n- **JAX-RS to Spring MVC mappings**:\n  - `@Path` → `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping`\n  - `@GET` → `@GetMapping`\n  - `@POST` → `@PostMapping`\n  - `@PUT` → `@PutMapping`\n  - `@DELETE` → `@DeleteMapping`\n  - `@PathParam` → `@PathVariable`\n  - `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam(required=false, defaultValue=\"\")`\n  - `@Context SecurityContext` → `@RequestAttribute(\"loggedUserId\") UUID`\n\n- **Dependency Injection**:\n  - `@Inject` (field injection) → Constructor injection\n  - Explicit constructors for proper `@Qualifier` support\n\n- **Transactions**:\n  - `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` → `org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional`\n\n- **Response Handling**:\n  - `Response.ok()` → `ResponseEntity.ok()`\n  - Manual JSON serialization using `ObjectMapper.writeValueAsString()` for wrapped responses\n  - Two ObjectMapper instances: regular for wrapped responses, `noWrapObjectMapper` for list responses\n\n- **Authentication**:\n  - Custom `@Authenticated` annotation (replacing `@Secured`)\n  - Spring HandlerInterceptor pattern (replacing JAX-RS ContainerRequestFilter)\n  - Request attribute pattern for passing authenticated user ID\n\nAll files are complete, compilable, and follow the Spring Boot patterns specified in the requirements. The old JAX-RS security infrastructure (Secured annotation, DecodedJWTSecurityContext, EmptySecurityContext) is now obsolete and can be deleted if needed."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"db1e3cb9-e8e1-4d47-8c79-8c5707bbed4e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015RrdjQQEmREeaPUfcJZvL7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All files have been created/updated. Now let me provide a comprehensive summary of the migration work completed.\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated the JAX-RS exception handling and serialization configuration from Jakarta EE to Spring Boot. Here's a detailed breakdown of all changes made:\n\n### 1. Exception Handling Migration\n\n**Created New File:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`\n\nThis new `@RestControllerAdvice` class replaces three JAX-RS `@Provider` exception mappers with a single Spring Boot exception handler. Key features:\n- Uses `@ExceptionHandler` methods for each exception type\n- Injects the `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` (with `@Qualifier`) to serialize error responses with root wrapping\n- Handles all infrastructure exceptions (UnauthorizedException, ForbiddenException)\n- Handles all business exceptions (UserNotFoundException, ArticleNotFoundException, TagNotFoundException, CommentNotFoundException, EmailAlreadyExistsException, UsernameAlreadyExistsException, InvalidPasswordException, ModelValidationException)\n- Handles validation exceptions (ConstraintViolationException, MethodArgumentNotValidException)\n- Handles malformed request body (HttpMessageNotReadableException)\n\n**Replaced Old Files** (now contain placeholder comments):\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java`\n\n### 2. ObjectMapper Configuration Migration\n\n**Updated File:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java`\n\nChanged from CDI annotations to Spring annotations with a three-bean strategy:\n\n1. **Primary ObjectMapper** (`@Primary @Bean objectMapper()`): Plain ObjectMapper used by Spring MVC for automatic request/response serialization. No root wrapping to allow request body deserialization with wrapper classes.\n\n2. **wrapRootValueObjectMapper** (`@Bean(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`): ObjectMapper with `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` and `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled. Used for manual serialization in controllers when responses need root wrapping (e.g., `{\"user\": {...}}`, `{\"article\": {...}}`).\n\n3. **noWrapRootValueObjectMapper** (`@Bean(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`): Plain ObjectMapper without root wrapping. Used for list responses that don't need wrapping (e.g., `{\"articles\": [...], \"articlesCount\": 5}`).\n\n**Important Note for Controller Migration:** Controllers should inject ObjectMappers as follows:\n- Original `objectMapper` (with wrapping) → `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n- Original `noWrapObjectMapper` (no wrapping) → `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper`\n\n### 3. Request Model Cleanup\n\n**Removed JSON-B imports from:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/request/NewArticleRequest.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/request/UpdateArticleRequest.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/request/NewCommentRequest.java`\n\nRemoved the unused `import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;` import from these files. This was a JSON-B annotation not available in Spring Boot's Jackson-based serialization.\n\n### 4. Qualifier Migration\n\n**Updated File:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/qualifiers/NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper.java`\n\nReplaced the CDI `@Qualifier` annotation with a placeholder comment. Spring Boot uses `@Qualifier(\"beanName\")` on injection points instead of custom qualifier annotations.\n\n### 5. Validation Files (No Changes Needed)\n\nThe following files already use `jakarta.validation.*` which is compatible with Spring Boot 3:\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/validation/constraint/AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/validation/validator/AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator.java`\n\nThese files remain unchanged and work seamlessly with Spring Boot's validation framework.\n\n### 6. Exception Classes (No Changes Needed)\n\nAll exception classes are simple POJOs extending RuntimeException and require no changes:\n- Infrastructure exceptions (UnauthorizedException, ForbiddenException, InfrastructureException)\n- Business exceptions (All domain exceptions with `getMessages()` method)\n\n### Key Migration Points\n\n1. **JAX-RS → Spring Boot**: Replaced `@Provider` with `@RestControllerAdvice` and `ExceptionMapper<T>` with `@ExceptionHandler` methods\n2. **CDI → Spring DI**: Replaced `@ApplicationScoped`, `@Singleton`, `@Produces`, `@Inject` with `@Configuration`, `@Bean`, `@Primary`, and constructor injection\n3. **HTTP Response**: Changed from JAX-RS `Response` to Spring's `ResponseEntity<String>`\n4. **JSON-B → Jackson**: Removed JSON-B imports (JsonbNillable) that are incompatible with Spring Boot\n5. **Qualifier Pattern**: Changed from custom `@Qualifier` annotation to Spring's `@Qualifier(\"beanName\")` approach\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated and are ready for use with Spring Boot 3!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"65321fc4-d5b9-43f2-b946-a7fd72b8e99a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01UjDBeFXJMohAUT3YAs9bQp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Qhdtk4VFzpjF2bqNgGCrPu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n\nimport com.auth0.jwt.JWT;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.JWTCreator;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.JWTVerifier;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.algorithms.Algorithm;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.Claim;\nimport com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\nimport java.util.Calendar;\nimport java.util.Date;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Component\npublic class JwtTokenProvider implements TokenProvider {\n\n    private final String COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION = \"complementary-subscription\";\n    private final String CLAIM_ROLES = \"ROLES\";\n    private Algorithm algorithm;\n    private JWTVerifier jwtVerifier;\n    private String issuer;\n    private Integer expirationTimeInMinutes;\n\n    public JwtTokenProvider(\n            @Value(\"${jwt.issuer}\") String issuer,\n            @Value(\"${jwt.secret}\") String secret,\n            @Value(\"${jwt.expiration.time.minutes}\") Integer expirationTimeInMinutes) {\n\n        this.issuer = issuer;\n        this.algorithm = Algorithm.HMAC512(secret);\n        this.jwtVerifier = JWT.require(algorithm).withIssuer(issuer).build();\n        this.expirationTimeInMinutes = expirationTimeInMinutes;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n        JWTCreator.Builder builder;\n\n        builder =\n                JWT.create()\n                        .withIssuer(issuer)\n                        .withSubject(subject)\n                        .withIssuedAt(new Date())\n                        .withClaim(COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION, UUID.randomUUID().toString());\n\n        builder.withArrayClaim(CLAIM_ROLES, toArrayNames(Role.USER));\n\n        if (expirationTimeInMinutes != null) {\n            builder.withExpiresAt(plusMinutes(expirationTimeInMinutes));\n        }\n\n        return builder.sign(algorithm);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public DecodedJWT verify(String token) {\n        return jwtVerifier.verify(token);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Role[] extractRoles(DecodedJWT decodedJWT) {\n        Claim claim = decodedJWT.getClaim(CLAIM_ROLES);\n        return claim.asArray(Role.class);\n    }\n\n    private static String[] toArrayNames(Role... allowedRoles) {\n\n        String[] names = new String[allowedRoles.length];\n\n        for (int nameIndex = 0; nameIndex < allowedRoles.length; nameIndex++) {\n            names[nameIndex] = allowedRoles[nameIndex].name();\n        }\n\n        return names;\n    }\n\n    private static Date plusMinutes(int minutes) {\n        int oneMinuteInMillis = 60000;\n        Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();\n        return new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis() + (minutes * oneMinuteInMillis));\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_read_input_tokens":80953,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":277,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1923},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"40bd3887-a4e0-4e46-8bdf-efce6ca03cab"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01UjDBeFXJMohAUT3YAs9bQp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RF7ia92Yf4BZq3V5Vmp24C","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/BCryptHashProvider.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n\nimport at.favre.lib.crypto.bcrypt.BCrypt;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n\n    @Override\n    public String hashPassword(String password) {\n        return BCrypt.withDefaults().hashToString(12, password.toCharArray());\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n        return BCrypt.verifyer().verify(plaintext.toCharArray(), hashed).verified;\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":277,"cache_read_input_tokens":80953,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":277,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1923},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TrtD1tKbaKwmrGzynjzvXR","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"b575a466-559d-4d55-8452-e28d3a37c78f"}
