{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHorynjTaxTQbxDNJ6bhJJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.UUID;\n    12→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    13→\n    14→@Service\n    15→public class ResourceUtils {\n    16→\n    17→    private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    18→    private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    20→    private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    21→    private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    22→    private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    23→\n    24→    public ResourceUtils(\n    25→            FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    26→            IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser,\n    27→            FindArticleTags findArticleTags,\n    28→            IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited,\n    29→            ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount) {\n    30→        this.findUserByUsername = findUserByUsername;\n    31→        this.isFollowingUser = isFollowingUser;\n    32→        this.findArticleTags = findArticleTags;\n    33→        this.isArticleFavorited = isArticleFavorited;\n    34→        this.articleFavoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount;\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    38→        final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    39→        final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    40→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    41→            profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    42→        }\n    43→        return profileResponse;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    47→        final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    48→        final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    49→        final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    50→        final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    51→        final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    52→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    53→            articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    54→        }\n    55→        return articleResponse;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    59→        final var resultResponse = pageResult.getResult().stream().map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    60→        return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    64→        final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    65→        final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    66→        return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    70→        final var resultResponse = comments.stream().map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    71→        return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    75→        return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    76→    }\n    77→}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"1fb258c6-1883-4846-8e1c-08c207a63214"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017YWu62cVLPdX1bF3yfwJHh","type":"tool_result","content":"src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/ArticleResponse.java:18:@JsonRootName(\"article\")\nsrc/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/UserResponse.java:12:@JsonRootName(\"user\")\nsrc/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/ProfileResponse.java:10:@JsonRootName(\"profile\")\nsrc/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/ErrorResponse.java:12:@JsonRootName(\"errors\")\nsrc/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/model/response/CommentResponse.java:16:@JsonRootName(\"comment\")"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"54c35185-a10e-49b5-940b-809d715af35a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Nzqr4GA8JfbxvKP46ZyMqq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. The response models with `@JsonRootName` are: `ArticleResponse(\"article\")`, `UserResponse(\"user\")`, `ProfileResponse(\"profile\")`, `ErrorResponse(\"errors\")`, `CommentResponse(\"comment\")`. These need the `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` to produce the root wrapping.\n\nLet me now fix all the controllers and delete obsolete files in parallel using multiple agents."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1986,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1384,"cache_read_input_tokens":40241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1384,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2526},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"52a30ab6-7961-4bd5-9734-038b2054db00"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Nzqr4GA8JfbxvKP46ZyMqq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_016aTE4wwBBYV5XGmfaqr9zt","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix controller ObjectMapper qualifiers","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need you to fix ObjectMapper qualifiers in several Spring controller files. The issue is that controllers manually serialize responses using `objectMapper.writeValueAsString()`, but they inject the primary (plain) ObjectMapper. Responses with `@JsonRootName` annotations (like `UserResponse`, `ArticleResponse`, `ProfileResponse`, `CommentResponse`, `ErrorResponse`) need the `wrapRootValueObjectMapper` to produce correct JSON like `{\"user\":{...}}`.\n\nHere are the files to edit:\n\n## 1. ArticlesResource.java\nFile: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java`\n\nChanges needed:\n- The `objectMapper` field (used for wrapped responses) needs `@Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` in the constructor\n- Remove the unused import `import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;`\n- The `noWrapObjectMapper` with `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")` is already correct\n\nCurrent constructor parameters:\n```java\n    public ArticlesResource(\n            ...\n            ObjectMapper objectMapper,\n            @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper) {\n```\n\nShould be:\n```java\n    public ArticlesResource(\n            ...\n            @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper,\n            @Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper) {\n```\n\n## 2. UsersResource.java\nFile: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java`\n\nAdd qualifier to constructor:\n```java\n    public UsersResource(\n            CreateUser createUser,\n            LoginUser loginUser,\n            TokenProvider tokenProvider,\n            @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n```\nAnd add import: `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;`\n\n## 3. UserResource.java\nFile: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`\n\nAdd qualifier to constructor:\n```java\n    public UserResource(\n            FindUserById findUserById,\n            UpdateUser updateUser,\n            TokenProvider tokenProvider,\n            @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n```\nAnd add import: `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;`\n\n## 4. ProfilesResource.java\nFile: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`\n\nAdd qualifier to constructor:\n```java\n    public ProfilesResource(\n            FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername,\n            UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername,\n            ResourceUtils resourceUtils,\n            @Qualifier(\"wrapRootValueObjectMapper\") ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n```\nAnd add import: `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;`\n\nPlease make ALL these edits using the Edit tool. Read each file first if needed, then make the edits."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1986,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1384,"cache_read_input_tokens":40241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1384,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2526},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"45f1855a-6190-47f4-b03c-cbc7804a6fdb"}
