{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TyhpPPjQdYDTB3FH3pf6uQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.domain.EntityScan;\n     6→import org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\n     7→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\n     8→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.EnableTransactionManagement;\n     9→\n    10→@SpringBootApplication\n    11→@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi\")\n    12→@EntityScan(basePackages = \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity\")\n    13→@EnableTransactionManagement\n    14→public class App {\n    15→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    16→        SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);\n    17→    }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"73a2a8e8-60a6-46b8-bdec-63e0e4e4acdd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015hDG4wq3bA4H5JnQdEEjhQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.port=8080\n     2→server.servlet.context-path=/api\n     3→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/postgres_db\n     4→spring.datasource.username=postgres_user\n     5→spring.datasource.password=S3cret\n     6→spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver\n     7→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     8→spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n     9→spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect\n    10→spring.jackson.serialization.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n    11→spring.jackson.deserialization.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE=false\n    12→jwt.issuer=users-service\n    13→jwt.secret=secret123\n    14→jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"065c548f-19f8-4a5a-9aa3-f7f36c8fbd44"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VbevpPtSid4tFjJYTyD7E1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.config;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter.AuthenticationFilter;\n     4→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     5→import org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.CorsRegistry;\n     6→import org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.InterceptorRegistry;\n     7→import org.springframework.web.servlet.config.annotation.WebMvcConfigurer;\n     8→\n     9→@Configuration\n    10→public class WebMvcConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {\n    11→\n    12→    private final AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter;\n    13→\n    14→    public WebMvcConfig(AuthenticationFilter authenticationFilter) {\n    15→        this.authenticationFilter = authenticationFilter;\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public void addInterceptors(InterceptorRegistry registry) {\n    20→        registry.addInterceptor(authenticationFilter);\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public void addCorsMappings(CorsRegistry registry) {\n    25→        registry.addMapping(\"/**\")\n    26→                .allowedOrigins(\"*\")\n    27→                .allowedMethods(\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\")\n    28→                .allowedHeaders(\"*\")\n    29→                .maxAge(3600);\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"5b7158c3-70de-4ae7-