{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lk7rvAE5mmeLzvggu84ar8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.Getter;\n     4→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     5→import lombok.Setter;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.UpdateArticleInput;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→@NoArgsConstructor\n    14→@AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull\n    15→public class UpdateArticleRequest {\n    16→\n    17→    private String title;\n    18→\n    19→    private String description;\n    20→\n    21→    private String body;\n    22→\n    23→    public UpdateArticleInput toUpdateArticleInput(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    24→        return new UpdateArticleInput(authorId, slug, this.title, this.description, this.body);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LVy4EVwizQwsKRjJE64712","session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"96c9d8f9-2d24-476b-8313-1056897c6211"}
