{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012uatoiRNQBg4xtiGXgJkK4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n     5→\n     6→public interface TokenProvider {\n     7→\n     8→    String createUserToken(String subject);\n     9→\n    10→    DecodedJWT verify(String token);\n    11→\n    12→    Role[] extractRoles(DecodedJWT decodedJWT);\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"0aff958e-2032-46e2-80a7-6c12ce75dc8e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011BQSJy28gDXnEfLUYnqpZA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.JWT;\n     4→import com.auth0.jwt.JWTCreator;\n     5→import com.auth0.jwt.JWTVerifier;\n     6→import com.auth0.jwt.algorithms.Algorithm;\n     7→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.Claim;\n     8→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    11→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\n    12→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.Calendar;\n    15→import java.util.Date;\n    16→import java.util.UUID;\n    17→\n    18→@Component\n    19→public class JwtTokenProvider implements TokenProvider {\n    20→\n    21→    private final String COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION = \"complementary-subscription\";\n    22→    private final String CLAIM_ROLES = \"ROLES\";\n    23→    private Algorithm algorithm;\n    24→    private JWTVerifier jwtVerifier;\n    25→    private String issuer;\n    26→    private Integer expirationTimeInMinutes;\n    27→\n    28→    public JwtTokenProvider(\n    29→            @Value(\"${jwt.issuer}\") String issuer,\n    30→            @Value(\"${jwt.secret}\") String secret,\n    31→            @Value(\"${jwt.expiration.time.minutes}\") Integer expirationTimeInMinutes) {\n    32→\n    33→        this.issuer = issuer;\n    34→        this.algorithm = Algorithm.HMAC512(secret);\n    35→        this.jwtVerifier = JWT.require(algorithm).withIssuer(issuer).build();\n    36→        this.expirationTimeInMinutes = expirationTimeInMinutes;\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @Override\n    40→    public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    41→        JWTCreator.Builder builder;\n    42→\n    43→        builder =\n    44→                JWT.create()\n    45→                        .withIssuer(issuer)\n    46→                        .withSubject(subject)\n    47→                        .withIssuedAt(new Date())\n    48→                        .withClaim(COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION, UUID.randomUUID().toString());\n    49→\n    50→        builder.withArrayClaim(CLAIM_ROLES, toArrayNames(Role.USER));\n    51→\n    52→        if (expirationTimeInMinutes != null) {\n    53→            builder.withExpiresAt(plusMinutes(expirationTimeInMinutes));\n    54→        }\n    55→\n    56→        return builder.sign(algorithm);\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public DecodedJWT verify(String token) {\n    61→        return jwtVerifier.verify(token);\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @Override\n    65→    public Role[] extractRoles(DecodedJWT decodedJWT) {\n    66→        Claim claim = decodedJWT.getClaim(CLAIM_ROLES);\n    67→        return claim.asArray(Role.class);\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    private static String[] toArrayNames(Role... allowedRoles) {\n    71→\n    72→        String[] names = new String[allowedRoles.length];\n    73→\n    74→        for (int nameIndex = 0; nameIndex < allowedRoles.length; nameIndex++) {\n    75→            names[nameIndex] = allowedRoles[nameIndex].name();\n    76→        }\n    77→\n    78→        return names;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    private static Date plusMinutes(int minutes) {\n    82→        int oneMinuteInMillis = 60000;\n    83→        Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();\n    84→        return new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis() + (minutes * oneMinuteInMillis));\n    85→    }\n    86→}\n    87→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1968c9d1-9222-41bb-9d6c-3e0081e3cb16","uuid":"837a90c8-a645-4374-8fa0-dcb1d183d1a7"}
